<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Introduction Request</title>
    <style>
      /* Add your CSS styles here */
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        background-color: #f4f4f4;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }
      p {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #fff;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }
      .button {
        display: inline-block;
        background-color: #4caf50;
        border: none;
        color: white;
        padding: 10px 25px;
        text-align: center;
        text-decoration: none;
        display: inline-block;
        font-size: 16px;
        margin: 4px 2px;
        cursor: pointer;
        border-radius: 8px;
      }
      .button:hover {
        background-color: #45a049;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Hello <%= recipientName %>,</h2>
      <p>
        I wanted to connect with <%= contactName %> of <%= companyName %>. <%=
        companyName %> is one of our top prospects as we work with few other
        companies in this space. Weâ€™d love to highlight how we can add value by
        working with them. Can you kindly facilitate an introduction between us?
      </p>
      <p>Regards,</p>
      <p><%= senderName %></p>
      <div>
        <form action="/handle-response" method="POST">
          <input type="hidden" name="recipient" value="<%= recipientEmail %>" />
          <input type="hidden" name="contact" value="<%= contactName %>" />
          <input type="hidden" name="company" value="<%= companyName %>" />
          <input type="hidden" name="sender" value="<%= senderName %>" />
          <button class="button" type="submit" name="response" value="Yes">
            Yes
          </button>
          <button class="button" type="submit" name="response" value="Can try">
            Can try
          </button>
          <button
            class="button"
            type="submit"
            name="response"
            value="No, Sorry!"
          >
            No, Sorry!
          </button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
